    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for module.delve, module.golang, delve, golang.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 8.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "Go Toolset provides the Go programming language tools and libraries. Go is alternatively known as golang. \n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* os/exec: Unexpected paths returned from LookPath in os/exec (CVE-2025-47906)\n\n* golang: archive/tar: Unbounded allocation when parsing GNU sparse map (CVE-2025-58183)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
